H0.text: Central nervous system is the system that includes the brain and spinal cord.

H1.text: Large nervous system is the system of which the brain and spinal cord are part.

H2.text: The cerebral cortex is the system that the brain and spinal cord are part of.

H3.text: The limbic system is the system that the brain and spinal cord are a part of.

A4.text: The central nervous system (CNS) is the part of the nervous system consisting primarily of the brain, spinal cord and retina.

A5.text: The CNS consists of two major structures: the brain and spinal cord.
